<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08055c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08055c">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08055c"> 55(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> flung overboard</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">L&apos;homme sup&eacute;rieur est celui qui conna&icirc;t le prix de l&apos;ordre, mais qui sait, &agrave; l&apos;occasion, jeter du lest, subordonner une petite n&eacute;cessit&eacute; &agrave; une plus grande, tel un capitaine de navire qui jette d&eacute;lib&eacute;rement &agrave; la mer la cargaison pour sauver le b&acirc;timent. <br><font color="green">[The superior man is he who knows the value of order, but who knows, when the need arises, to throw off the ballast, to subordinate a small need to a greater one, like the captain of a ship who deliberately casts his cargo into the sea to save the structure.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 217</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
